            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Book recommendation: Wintering",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/01/https---bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com-public-images-44f05908-5f00-4a31-a873-8a6f8892aeec_317x500.jpeg",
        "width": 317,
        "height": 500
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And, while we're talking about books, here's a recommendation. It was the last book I read in 2020, and it was perfect timing. It’s not just a book about surviving winter, but weathering the difficult and lost moments in your life. The writing is exquisite, drawing you in and making reading on an effortless glide. Under a broadly chronological structure, the book hops around time and location, exploring the issues that arise from a particularly difficult winter in the author’s life.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In many ways, this book is the ultimate antidote to the toxic startup culture that seems to have infected business spilling out of the Silicon Valley VC world. Rather than hustling harder and faster, and throwing any extra energy into a side hustle, this book explores the periods of our lives when we need to conserve energy — and money — survive the storm, and be ready for the next spring.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Life is cyclical, not linear. And this book will truly help you understand what that could mean for the way you live.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
